  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oil in a deep frying pan to 375°F.",
    "Combine ground beef, onion, ginger, cilantro, lime juice, and garam masala in a bowl.",
    "Mix well and set aside.",
    "Unfold pastry and cut into triangles.",
    "Place 1-2 tablespoons of the beef mixture onto the center of each pastry triangle.",
    "Brush the edges with water and fold the pastry into a triangle, pressing the edges to seal.",
    "Fry the samosas until golden brown, about 3-4 minutes on each side.",
    "Drain on paper towels and serve hot."
